detail_description: Black Ginger is a modern Thai restaurant located at The Slate Resort in Phuket. Accessible only by boat, this unique dining experience begins with a romantic raft ride through the hotel's lagoon to a traditional Thai house. Chef Anongrat Piak Meklai offers avant-garde Thai cuisine, featuring dishes like Moo Hong and Beef Massaman. The restaurant's dark interior creates an elegant atmosphere for guests to enjoy their meal.
name: Black Ginger | Thai Restaurant | The Slate, Phuket
address: 116, อําเภ, Sakhu, Thalang District, Phuket 83110, Thailand

excerpt: Traditional dishes are served in this acclaimed restaurant set in a Colonial-style building.
detail_description: Nestled in a charming Colonial-style building, One Chun Cafe & Restaurant is a must-visit for anyone seeking authentic Phuketian and Southern Thai cuisine. This beloved eatery has garnered attention for its traditional dishes that evoke nostalgia with every bite. As you step inside, you'll notice the unique cash-only policy, which adds to its old-world charm. The friendly staff includes a waiter fluent in Chinese, ensuring that all guests feel welcome and can easily navigate the menu.
name: One Chun Cafe & Restaurant
address: 48, 1 Thep Krasattri Rd, Talat Yai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: The Blue Elephant Cooking School & Restaurant in Phuket is located in a beautifully restored Sino-Portuguese mansion that was once the residence of a prominent Chinese merchant. The restaurant offers signature dishes found at all Blue Elephant locations, as well as an impressive selection of Peranakan cuisine, thanks to a collaboration with a Peranakan association and Rajabhat Phuket University.
name: Blue Elephant Phuket Cooking School & Restaurant
address: Krabi Road 96, Talat Nuea, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Suay Cherngtalay is a renowned Thai-fusion restaurant located in Phuket, offering a unique dining experience with traditional Thai dishes infused with international flavors. The menu features creative dishes like Foie Gras Bites Thai Style and Tuna Tartar in Thai Style, as well as Sea Bass Steak and Coconut Prawn with Green Curry Sauce. The restaurant's intimate ambiance includes indoor and outdoor dining areas, a counter bar, and a BBQ terrace.
name: Suay Cherngtalay
address: 4, 177/99 Moo 6, Si Sunthon, Thalang District, Phuket 83110, Thailand

excerpt: Inviting, century-old building offering authentic Phuketian cooking & elevated wine & cocktails.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Old Phuket Town, Tu Kab Khao Restaurant is a charming gem housed in a century-old building that exudes history and character. This delightful eatery specializes in authentic Southern Thai cuisine, offering an array of traditional dishes alongside unique creations like mackerel soup with tamarind and red crab meat curry. The inviting interior features plush sofa chairs and warm lighting, creating a cozy yet elegant dining atmosphere.
name: Tu Kab Khao Restaurant Phuket
address: 8 Phangnga Rd, Tambon Talat Yai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Acqua Restaurant, situated at the north end of Patong on Kalim Beach, is a top choice for those seeking an exquisite Italian dining experience in Phuket. Renowned for its fresh seafood and traditional Italian flavors, this award-winning restaurant offers a menu curated by Sardinian chef Alessandro Frau.
name: Acqua Restaurant
address: 324, 15 Phrabaramee Rd, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: La Gritta, located in Patong Beach at Amari Coral Beach, offers an elegant dining experience with a wide-ranging modern Italian menu. The restaurant's seafront setting provides breathtaking views and warm tropical breezes under a starry night sky. From antipasti and Italian meats to pastas and pizza, La Gritta's menu will transport you to the picture-perfect island of Capri.
name: La Gritta
address: Amari, 2 Muen-ngern Road Beach, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Raya Restaurant, located in Phuket Old Town, is a century-old establishment with original mosaic-tiled floors and walls adorned with vintage tea and coffee posters as well as images of Thai monarchs.
name: Raya Restaurant
address: 48/1 Dibuk Rd, Tambon Talat Yai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Nestled on the stunning Kata Beach with breathtaking views of the Andaman Sea and lush Thai forests, Mom Tri's Kitchen is a renowned dining destination in Phuket. The restaurant offers a blend of modern and traditional Thai dishes paired with creative cocktails crafted by expert mixologists. Whether it's a romantic date night or a special dinner, this elegant establishment provides an unforgettable experience.
name: Mom Tri's Kitchen
address: R75W+XVH, Karon, Mueang, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

detail_description: Tucked away near Karon Beach, The Pad Thai Shop may seem unassuming with its simple decor and plastic chairs, but it's renowned for its piping hot and generous servings of delicious pad Thai. Locals and tourists alike seek out this streetside gem for its signature dish, though the menu also offers noodle soup and pad krapao. For a change of pace, visitors can enjoy delicately spiced North Indian cuisine at the nearby orange-walled restaurant with wooden tables.
name: The Pad Thai Shop
address: 12, 3, Tambon Karon, เมือง, Phuket 83100, Thailand

excerpt: Classic seafood dishes in a popular, informal eatery with tables overlooking a mangrove swamp.
detail_description: Mor Mu Dong Restaurant is a hidden gem in east Phuket, offering a secluded and rustic dining experience surrounded by a mangrove swamp. Despite being difficult to locate, it has garnered attention from food enthusiasts and renowned writers like Andrew Zimmern. The restaurant's network of bamboo huts provides serene river views, making it an ideal spot for a peaceful meal.
name: Mor Mu Dong Restaurant
address: 9/4 หมู่ที่ 3 ซอย ป่าหล่าย ถนน เจ้าฟ้า, Chalong, อำเภอ เมืองภูเก็ต, Phuket 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Phuket, Red Duck Restaurant may be small in size but it delivers big on flavor. The owner and chef's personal touch ensures a memorable dining experience, with classic Thai dishes prepared to perfection and served with elegance. With a cozy ambiance and only a handful of tables, this boutique restaurant offers an intimate setting for enjoying authentic Phuket cuisine with a Western twist.
name: Red Duck Restaurant
address: 86, 136 Soi Saiyuan, Rawai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83130, Thailand

detail_description: Nestled in the eastern part of Phuket Town, Ko Ang Seafood is a beloved dining spot celebrated for its delectable array of seafood. What began as a modest eatery with a simple zinc roof has blossomed into an inviting restaurant adorned with charming Chinese decor, all while retaining its local allure. This long-standing establishment has garnered praise for its diverse menu, featuring not only classic seafood dishes but also more adventurous offerings such as red ant eggs and palm grubs.
name: Ko Ang Seafood
address: 226 หมู่ 2 Phuket Rd, Tambon Talat Yai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand

detail_description: Baan Rim Pa, which means "The House by the Cliff," is a locally owned restaurant located at the northern tip of Patong. It offers a unique dining experience with high-quality local cuisine. The menu features a wide variety of royal Thai dishes, including popular options like Green Curry and Grilled fresh Tiger Prawns. This establishment has been serving guests for over a generation and is known for offering authentic Royal Thai cuisine that was once exclusive to Thailand's Grand Palace.
name: Baan Rim Pa ... (Ban Rim Pha)
address: 249/4 Prabaramee Road, Kalim, Pa Tong, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Boathouse Restaurant in Cherngtalay offers a unique dining experience with a blend of traditional Thai dishes and international flavors. The menu features creative dishes like Foie Gras Bites Thai Style, Tuna Tartar in Thai Style, Sea Bass Steak, Rice Berry Risotto, Coconut Prawn and Green Curry Sauce. The restaurant's interior design provides an intimate ambiance with indoor and outdoor dining areas, a counter bar, and BBQ terrace.
name: The Boathouse Restaurant
address: Karon, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83100, Thailand

detail_description: Sam's Steaks and Grill in Patong, Phuket, stands out by focusing on succulent steaks and grilled meats rather than the area's typical seafood. The restaurant offers a modern and elegant atmosphere where beachwear is not permitted. With top cuts of Wagyu beef and prime steaks imported from Australia, it provides great value for money. The stylish decor, friendly staff, and good service create an awesome dining experience.
name: Sam's Steaks and Grill
address: 52 Thawewong Rd, Pa Tong, Amphoe Kathu, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Ta Khai, located within the Trisara Resort in Phuket, offers a charming and rustic dining experience with a focus on seafood made from fresh local ingredients. The restaurant's name means 'fishing net', reflecting its emphasis on seafood dishes. The menu features flavorful dishes with slightly toned-down spicing for Western palates, and two set menus provide a variety of options to try. Guests can enjoy the beautiful setting and terrace seating while savoring authentic Thai cuisine.
name: Ta Khai
address: 88/28, 88/30-30, Muen-Ngern Rd In Rosewood, Muen-Ngern Rd, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Jaras Restaurant is an upscale dining establishment located at The Intercontinental Phuket in Kamala Beach, Thailand. It has earned a place in the Michelin Guide for its superbly presented modern Thai cuisine. The restaurant prides itself on using only the freshest and top-quality ingredients to create delicious, well-balanced dishes that are beautifully presented. Guests can expect excellent service from the accommodating staff, along with an impressive wine list featuring high-end options at reasonable prices.
name: Jaras Restaurant
address: 333, 333/3, Kamala, Kathu District, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Sizzle Rooftop Restaurant is a perfect choice for those who love grilled dishes. The menu offers a wide variety of steaks, including beef tenderloin and beef strip loin, as well as Kurobuta pork chops, grill-roasted chicken, and seafood items. The restaurant also boasts an impressive selection of mid-priced and premium wines from around the world.
name: Sizzle Rooftop Restaurant
address: Beach, 39/9 Muen-Ngern Rd, Tambon Patong, Amphoe Kathu, Phuket 83150, Thailand

detail_description: Kopitiam by Wilai is a charming cafe located in Phuket Old Town, offering traditional kopi and a variety of snacks at affordable prices. Situated on the historic Thalang road, it provides an ideal spot to relax and recharge after exploring the area. The cafe's vintage-style ambiance pays homage to the Peranakan community, with nostalgic Nyonya dishes like bak kut teh and slow-cooked massaman curry on offer.
name: Kopitiam by Wilai
address: 18 Thalang Rd, Tambon Talat Yai, Mueang Phuket District, Phuket 83000, Thailand
